题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1333" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-03/de844380-a47d-11ec-b6be-9dd2ff775c4e" width="2000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Nathan Ingraham / Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Apple iPad Air (2022)]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Apple iPad Air (2022)]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Ford will offer flexible Mustang Mach-E leases to Uber drivers in three cities]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>当 Uber 司机想换用<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/uber-rents-tesla-evs-to-drivers-131556170.html">电动汽车时，他们不仅可以轻松使用特斯拉</a>汽车。福特和优步正在启动一项扩展的 Drive 试点计划，为洛杉矶、圣地亚哥和旧金山的拼车司机提供灵活的<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/fords-upgraded-mustang-mach-e-offers-more-range-at-a-lower-price-161151398.html">Mustang Mach-E</a>租赁服务。运营商以一到四个月的增量选择租约，并在两周内获得他们的 Mach-E。之后，他们使用 Ford Drive 应用程序来处理付款和维护。与此同时，福特从经销商处购买电动跨界车车队并将其用于维修。</p><p>租赁费用为每周 199 美元，含 500 英里，每周 249 美元，含 1,000 英里。超出计划提供的里程，司机每多付 20 美分。这可能看起来很昂贵，但福特指望轻松退出和续约作为平局。优步员工只有在有足够的驾驶时间来证明费用合理时才可以租赁。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>福特和优步去年在圣地亚哥首次测试了 Drive，车队中有 150 多辆 Mustang Mach-E 汽车。这些公司没有说明最初的运行有多成功，但他们指出加州是优步对电动汽车需求的最佳市场。福特表示，截至 2022 年底，近 10% 的乘客里程是在电动汽车中完成的。</p><p>要获得资格，司机需要至少有 4.85 星评级和超过 150 次旅行。提供的 Mustang 是一款简洁的后轮驱动车型，续航里程为 247 英里，但它确实配备了 CoPilot360 驾驶辅助系统。</p><p>租赁选项符合 Uber 到 2030 年在北美和欧洲成为零排放服务的目标。从理论上讲，这使得电动汽车对于无法承诺购买或多年租赁的司机来说更加可行。优步还通过每次乘车额外支付 1 美元（每年高达 4,000 美元）和为优质 Comfort Electric 乘客提供服务的选项来增加这一提议。并不是说优步有太多选择。加州将要求到 2030 年<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/california-rule-ride-hailing-ev-2030-072036470.html">大多数网约车都是电动的</a>，而纽约市则希望在同年实现<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/new-york-city-uber-lyft-electric-cars-2030-222628210.html">大规模转型</a>。</p><p>与此同时，福特通过将 Mach-E 交到拼车司机手中而受益，否则他们会通过 Hertz 租用特斯拉电动汽车。这也提高了该品牌在乘客中的曝光度，并有助于福特将自己打造成一家通用移动公司。挑战只是与特斯拉的绝对数量竞争。与赫兹的交易将在美国道路上投放多达 50,000 辆特斯拉电动汽车，而福特的 Drive 试点将不会以目前的规模竞争。</p>本文最初出现在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/ford-will-offer-flexible-mustang-mach-e-leases-to-uber-drivers-in-three-cities-151534606.html?src =rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/ford-will-offer-flexible-mustang-mach-e-leases-to-uber-drivers-in-three-cities-151534606.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 106a6437-17fd-40f5-931c-35097dd6fa28</guid><dc:creator>乔恩·芬加斯</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Thu, 01 Jun 2023 15:15:34 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1685631546</ingested><modified> 2023-06-01T14:59:16+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Automotive Industry]]></category><category><![CDATA[Consumer Discretionary]]></category><category><![CDATA[Autos]]></category><category><![CDATA[Transportation]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Jon Fingas]]></category><media:content height="1280" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/72175980-0084-11ee-9eea-44b472dc5659" width="1920"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1280" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/72175980-0084-11ee-9eea-44b472dc5659" width="1920"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Ford]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Ford Mustang Mach-E in Uber pilot]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Ford Mustang Mach-E in Uber pilot]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Arturia's FX Collection 4 adds a Leslie rotary speaker emulator]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> Arturia 的<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/arturia-fx-collection-3-distortion-lo-fi-granular-effects-173429817.html">效果器合集</a>变得物超所值，尤其是当您想要重现经典声音时。该公司<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.arturia.com/products/software-effects/fx-collection/overview">发布了</a>一个 FX Collection 4 包，增加了四种效果，包括一个全新的 Rotary CLS-222 套件（上图），它使 Leslie 旋转扬声器模拟器现代化。它以乔治·哈里森和大卫·吉尔摩等吉他手使用的声音而闻名，也被爵士风琴手使用。</p><p> FX Collection 4 添加了您以前必须单独购买的效果器，包括<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/arturia-dist-coldfire-distortion-plugin-204028687.html">Dist Coldfire</a>失真插件、源自 Korg 的 Filter MS-20 和升级的<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/arturias-augmented-brass-plugin-is-built-for-synthwave-and-sci-fi-scores-150043349.html">Rev LX-24</a> 80 年代混响盒。对多个工具进行了调整，包括 40 个<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/arturia-efx-fragments-granular-vst-effect-193053457.html">Efx 片段</a>的新预设以及 Bus Force 和 Rev Spring-636 效果的新功能。您可能还会很高兴看到对 NKS VS3 和 Apple Silicon AAX 的支持。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>现在共有 30 种效果，包括受 SansAmp 踏板启发的 OpAmp-21、Dist Tube-Culture（传奇的 Thermionic Culture Vulture 失真单元的重复）和磁带仿真工具 Tape Mello-Fi。虽然这不会涵盖所有可能的需求，但您很有可能可以重现熟悉的声音或使普通乐器几乎无法辨认。</p><p>该公司以 399 美元的价格提供 FX Collection 4。就插件包而言，这并不是特别昂贵。您可能不需要购买太多其他东西来完成曲目。我们还要补充一点，Arturia 经常进行促销，因此值得留意潜在的折扣。</p>本文最初出现在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/arturias-fx-collection-4-adds-a-leslie-rotary-speaker-emulator-150009128.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/arturias-fx-collection-4-adds-a-leslie-rotary-speaker-emulator-150009128.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 81cbc950-09bd-4ca5-973a-278722ea1841</guid><dc:creator>乔恩·芬加斯</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Thu, 01 Jun 2023 15:00:09 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1685626345</ingested><modified> 2023-06-01T13:32:29+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Jon Fingas]]></category><media:content height="1080" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/e95b02d0-007a-11ee-bdcb-83532f07610f" width="1908"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1080" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/e95b02d0-007a-11ee-bdcb-83532f07610f" width="1908"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Arturia]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Arturia Rotary CLS-222 effects plugin]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Arturia Rotary CLS-222 effects plugin]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA['Street Fighter 6' gets the vibe right]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>没过多久我就爱上了<em>街头霸王 6</em> 。也许是在一场特别史诗般的 Drive Gauge 格挡中，它让我的电脑屏幕充满了爆炸性的色彩，或者是在玩<em>Yakuza</em>式的世界巡回赛时，当我在街上与 randos 打架时。在某个时候，我觉得自己又回到了家，组合成龙拳，用春丽无穷无尽的致命踢击造成破坏。<em>街头霸王 6</em>证明<em>街头霸王</em>又回来了——这是一款欢迎新粉丝并让老粉丝回归的游戏。</p><p>当我说老粉丝的时候，我指的是我自己。我记得当我第一次在当地的汉堡王看到<em>街头霸王 2</em>橱柜时的敬畏之情（我的家乡可悲的是没有街机）。这些精灵比我见过的要大，而且动画效果非常华丽。人物各不相同，充满个性。控件让我看到了超越单纯平台游戏的可能性。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> <em>Street Fighter 的</em>特殊动作经久不衰是有原因的：它们易于学习，但需要不断练习才能发挥作用。不过，如果足够好，他们就会开始觉得自己是自己的延伸。如果您是波道拳大师，您还不如让闪电在您的手指间噼啪作响。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/23ad4da2-0083-11ee-afbc-a31ddeaec0d8" style="height:1080px;width:1920px;" alt="Ryu 在街头霸王 6 中冲刺拳" data-uuid="add5f3b0-befa-388a-a3f2-da84754bbee3"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">卡普空</div></figure><p>为了向新观众开放， <em>《街头霸王 6》</em>对特殊动作采用了一种非凡的新方法。除了粉丝们喜爱的经典控制之外，还有一个“现代”方案，它极大地简化了按钮输入，还有“动态”控制，它基本上让你可以混合按钮让游戏的 AI 掌控方向盘。现代模式用轻、中、重攻击的三个按钮取代了六个独立的拳击和踢击按钮。还有一个独立的特殊移动按钮，可根据您握住方向键的方式激活不同的攻击。此更改为您在游戏手柄的表面提供了四个功能按钮，而不是像经典控件那样将一些攻击按钮推到肩按钮上。</p><p>虽然<em>街头霸王的</em>铁杆粉丝可能会谴责这些选项是淡化该系列的一种方式，但我认为它们对其生存至关重要。之前的作品<em>《街头霸王 V》</em>因迎合电子竞技玩家和其他顽固分子而受到广泛批评。传统的街机模式花了数年时间才出现，但到那时许多人已经注销了这款游戏。另一方面，<em>街头霸王 6</em>直接吸引了休闲粉丝和街头霸王好奇者。</p><p>这在新的 World Tour 模式中也很明显，该模式涉及设计您自己的战斗机以在类似纽约市的环境中进行一系列任务。它基本上是一款融合了 Yakuza 游戏的街头霸王角色扮演游戏：您将获得经验值并升级，您还可以挑战街上的人进行即兴比赛。结果几乎总是荒谬的——我从不厌倦看到无聊的商人倒下——但至关重要的是，它也真的很有趣。</p><p>早期，世界巡回赛还作为一种新玩家的互动培训模式。它可以帮助您了解现代格斗模式，以及巷战的一些细节。 Luke 也是<em>街头霸王 V</em>中最后一个引入的角色，也是这款游戏表面上的主角。作为一个老大哥，他既自大又乐于助人，这对新玩家来说是一个很有帮助的组合。 </p><div id="acc6ca38c10b461f9997e359d2d9f509"><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/nmv8HwUvc-k?rel=0" style="top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;position:absolute;border:0;" allowfullscreen="" scrolling="no"></iframe></div><p>甚至在您开始比赛之前， <em>《街头霸王 6》</em>就会散发出风格。开场菜单结合了城市霓虹灯和街头艺术，角色选择主题是一首朗朗上口（虽然有些古怪）的嘻哈曲调，每个舞台的音乐都让我的低音炮震耳欲聋。 <em>《街头霸王 6》</em>感觉就像一场邀请所有人参加的派对，气氛恰到好处。</p><p>也许这就是为什么我很难让自己远离现实世界，或者去玩其他游戏，比如<em>王国之泪</em>。街机模式非常轻松，可以在 10 分钟内完成。默认情况下，它包括四场格斗比赛和一场经典的车辆破坏小游戏，实际的游戏玩法比以往任何时候都更令人上瘾。和往常一样，玩街机游戏可以解锁角色的背景细节，但这一次您还可以获得经典的<em>街头霸王</em>艺术，其中大部分都击中了我 90 年代的怀旧之心。 </p><section data-eng-breakout="e52038475f4d441c9c4b556db27909de" data-eng-breakout-type="e2ehero"><img class="e2ehero-url" src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/23ad4da0-0083-11ee-b176-4edcca8aceae" style="height:720px;width:1280px;" alt="街头霸王 6 中的 Guile 拳打 Ryu"></section><p>除了通常的超级响应式<em>街头霸王</em>机制之外，还有一个 Drive Gauge 可以解锁大量新选项。你可以用它发起攻击，将你的对手扔到墙上（让他们容易受到一些令人满意的后续连击的攻击）、格挡攻击、在阻挡后扔出逆转并冲过屏幕。随着时间的推移和你自己的攻击会再生的驱动量表也可以用来给你的特殊动作更多的咬合力。所有的驱动机制都相对容易实现，它们通常只需要按下两个按钮，但学习如何部署它们需要一些时间。</p><p> Super Arts，需要更复杂的按钮输入的超级攻击，也回归了。 （否则，街头霸王<em>&nbsp;</em>玩家可能会再次反抗。）它们依赖于一个单独的超级仪表，除了造成大量伤害外，它们还可以用来摧毁你竞争对手的驱动仪表。</p><p>在我的 PC 上玩<em>街头霸王 6</em>时，我在 Xbox Elite 2 控制器和 Hori 街机摇杆之间切换，两种输入都感觉非常流畅。作为一个在 SNES 格斗游戏中长大的人，我更喜欢游戏手柄，但我也发现自己比平时更喜欢街机摇杆体验。 <em>Street Fighter 6 的</em>视觉效果、震撼的配乐和整体风格的结合让我感觉自己置身于真正的街机游戏中，而在我的办公桌上放一根战斗棒只会增强这种感觉。</p><p>除了 Luke 之外， <em>Street Fighter 6</em>还添加了新角色，例如柔道专家/超级名模 Manon（多么棒的概念！），以及衣冠楚楚的老战士 JP。我通常需要一段时间才能适应新角色，尤其是当我最近没有太多时间使用经典的<em>街头霸王</em>名册时，但所有新添加的内容都为特许经营带来了一些东西。一些人也向早期角色致敬：金伯利是前<em>Final Fight</em> ninja Guy 的学生； Lily 是 T. Hawke 的 Thunderfoot 部落的成员； Jamie 从 Yun 和 Yang 那里获得灵感。</p><p>至于在线游戏，我只能在短时间内尝试<em>《街头霸王 6》的</em>多人游戏，但我的所有比赛都感觉流畅且无延迟。当然，一旦成群结队的绝望玩家出现，体验可能会有所不同。一个新的专用战斗中心也可以作为一个在线空间，使用你的世界巡回赛头像与其他玩家互动。您可以在街机柜排队观看比赛，玩<em>《最终决战》</em>和<em>《街头霸王 2》</em>等老游戏，甚至可以与其他玩家的化身一起参加比赛。我喜欢 Battle Hub 的社交元素，它让多人比赛比仅仅与不露面的玩家排队更具吸引力。</p><p> <em>Street Fighter 6</em>的多种模式和战斗选项可能会让新玩家感到不知所措，但它最终是对让<em>Street Fighter</em>伟大的一切的庆祝。像<em>真人快打这样的特许经营</em>权有其极端的血腥和（令人惊讶的）强大的故事情节可以依赖。 Capcom 系列的乐趣一直在于与您的朋友一起出去玩，完善您的连击和特殊动作，并了解您最喜欢的角色的复杂性。<em>街头霸王 6</em>提醒人们，<em>街头霸王</em>适合所有人，这是一件值得一看的美好事物。</p>本文最初出现在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/street-fighter-6-gets-the-vibe-right-141559193.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/street-fighter-6-gets-the-vibe-right-141559193.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> e39cc756-13e9-4e57-a40c-b25c3363b465</guid><dc:creator>德文德拉·哈达瓦</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Thu, 01 Jun 2023 14:30:59 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1685632957</ingested><modified> 2023-06-01T15:22:47+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Consumer Discretionary]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Devindra Hardawar]]></category><media:content height="1080" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/23ad4da1-0083-11ee-9fc5-5ce67f915b8b" width="1920"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1080" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/23ad4da1-0083-11ee-9fc5-5ce67f915b8b" width="1920"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Capcom]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Kimberly kicking Luke in Street Fighter 6]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Street Fighter 6]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The Meta Quest 3 is a $499 mixed reality headset with full-color passthrough]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>马克·扎克伯格 (Mark Zuckerberg)<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.instagram.com/p/Cs809N-BUJ7/">发布了</a>Meta Quest 3，这是该公司<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/meta-project-cambria-details-vr-headset-roadmap-181023351.html">传闻已久的</a><a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/meta-quest-3-2023-233025187.html">下一代</a>虚拟现实耳机。 Meta CEO 在最新的<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/metas-next-quest-games-showcase-is-june-1st-165019399.html">Meta Quest Games Showcase</a>之前几个小时首次展示了该设备，就在 Apple 的 WWDC 之前。</p><p>与<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/meta-quest-pro-review-a-next-gen-headset-for-the-vr-faithful-specs-price-130045313.html">Quest Pro</a>一样， <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.meta.com/quest/">Quest 3</a>支持混合现实并提供全彩直通。这使用户能够通过外部摄像头看到他们周围物理空间的彩色版本。耳机将能够将增强现实元素融入外部世界。扎克伯格说这是“第一款具有高分辨率彩色混合现实的主流耳机”。 </p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><div id="0040c82cd433493397ce2a31c03d9b4a"><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/5AKl_cEB26c?rel=0" style="top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;position:absolute;border:0;" allowfullscreen="" scrolling="no"></iframe></div><p>扎克伯格声称该设备拥有“下一代”高通芯片组，它提供的图形性能是 Quest 2 的两倍。据说它是 Meta 的“迄今为止最强大的耳机”。 Meta 的首席执行官指出，尽管 Quest 3 具有额外的魅力，但它比其前身更舒适且薄 40%。</p><p> Meta 重新设计了 Quest 3 的控制器。它说它们更加流线型和符合人体工程学，并且它们结合了 Touch Pro 控制器中的 TruTouch 触觉反馈技术。新的 Touch Plus 控制器也不再有外部跟踪环。 Meta 说，这将帮助他们感觉自己的手更自然地延伸并且占用更少的空间。此外，Quest 3 将支持跳跃时的<a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2019-09-27-oculus-quest-hand-tracking-hands-on.html">手部追踪</a>。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/84ea8ed0-008c-11ee-b58f-226236aa2181" style="height:1080px;width:1920px;" alt="Meta Quest 3 Touch Plus 控制器" data-uuid="2a99e0ae-f3cf-3cd5-a695-238d4fb602a7"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">元</div></figure><p>这款耳机的起价为 500 美元，存储容量为 128GB，将于今年秋季在所有提供 Quest 2 的国家/地区上市。它的价格是<a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/meta-drops-the-price-of-its-quest-pro-vr-headset-to-999-153753541.html">Quest Pro</a>的一半，与<a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/playstation-vr2-review-great-headset-should-be-cheaper-130032254.html">PlayStation VR2</a> （用户需要将其插入 PS5）的价格相同。</p><p>与此同时，从 6 月 4 日开始，Quest 2 的基本 128GB 版本将再次花费 300 美元。 256GB 型号售价 350 美元。 Meta 去年<a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/meta-quest-2-price-increase-180745817.html">将该耳机的价格提高了 100 美元</a>，原因是制造成本增加。扎克伯格当时表示，3 月份，它将 256GB Quest 2 的价格降低了 70 美元至 429 美元，以帮助“更多人进入 VR”。</p><p>此外，即将推出的软件更新将提升 Quest 2 和 Quest Pro 的性能。 Meta 表示，每款头显的 CPU 性能提升高达 26%，GPU 在 Quest 2 上提升高达 19%，在 Quest Pro 上提升 11%。两个耳机也将启用动态分辨率缩放。根据 Meta 的说法，这将帮助他们“在不丢帧的情况下利用增加的像素密度”。 </p><div id="824e75d12ffe4139b26e1c9fdfdf2310"><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/c5sqUg7RvjM?rel=0" style="top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;position:absolute;border:0;" allowfullscreen="" scrolling="no"></iframe></div><p> Quest 3 将与每个 Quest 2 应用程序和体验完全兼容。该公司将在 9 月 27 日举行的 Connect 会议上透露更多细节，</p><p> Meta 推出 Quest 3 也就不足为奇了。 Earlier this week, <em>Bloomberg</em> &#39;s Mark Gurman said he&#39;d had <a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/metas-quest-3-headset-could-feature-color-cameras-for-more-lifelike-pass-through-video-155645837.html">hands-on time with a Quest 3 prototype</a> . Gurman wrote that the headset “feels far lighter and thinner” than the previous model and that it had a sturdier head strap. Unlike the Quest Pro, though, the Quest 3 may not have face or eye-tracking features.</p><p> In another year, Zuckerberg might have waited until Connect to reveal the Quest 3. However, Meta may be trying to steal some of Apple&#39;s thunder. The latter is <a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/apple-mixed-reality-headset-wwdc-2023-announcement-221042779.html">widely expected</a> to reveal a premium mixed-reality headset at WWDC next week. As such, Meta may soon be facing another major competitor in the mixed reality space.</p><p><core-commerce id="c25c487b967040808d4b4eb02c66aa20" data-type="product-list"></p><p></p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/the-meta-quest-3-is-a-499-mixed-reality-headset-with-full-color-passthrough-141204527.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/the-meta-quest-3-is-a-499-mixed-reality-headset-with-full-color-passthrough-141204527.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 2ce4dbf1-862b-4dcb-a4fa-30168d6b2171</guid><dc:creator>克里斯霍尔特</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Thu, 01 Jun 2023 14:12:04 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1685632245</ingested><modified> 2023-06-01T15:10:50+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Kris Holt]]></category><media:content height="639" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/e06e00e0-0085-11ee-bd3e-f25c4b1a4507" width="1170"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="639" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/e06e00e0-0085-11ee-bd3e-f25c4b1a4507" width="1170"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Meta]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Meta Quest 3]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Meta Quest 3]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[AMC transfers its on-demand streaming users to Vudu]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> AMC Entertainment&#39;s streaming service is migrating its users to Vudu. The companies announced today that Vudu is “the official new streaming platform for consumers of AMC Theatres on Demand.”</p><p> AMC launched its<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2019-10-15-amc-on-demand-streaming.html">on-demand streaming service</a> in 2019, and its popularity surged during pandemic-era lockdowns. In 2020, as moviegoers largely avoided theaters, the company <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/universal-amc-theater-window-222954241.html">partnered with Universal</a> to allow the studio&#39;s films to jump to premium video-on-demand (PVOD) platforms — including AMC&#39;s service — only 17 days after premiering in theaters. However, as viewing habits have readjusted in the last three years, AMC has now decided to offload the service to a frequent partner instead.</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> Vudu says AMC Theatres On Demand customers will have their content libraries automatically upgraded “to the highest quality format available on Vudu, including 4K Ultra HD.” In addition, new Vudu accounts moving from AMC&#39;s service will get 15 percent off every purchase for their first month on the platform.</p><p> Fandango Media, a joint venture between NBCUniversal and Warner Bros. Discovery, currently owns Vudu. Walmart <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2010-02-22-wal-mart-buying-vudu-streaming-movie-service.html">bought</a> the platform in 2010 and ran it for a decade before <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/fandango-vudu-deal-walmart-streaming-192652676.html">selling it to Fandango Media</a> in 2020 for an undisclosed amount. Its new owner then rolled FandangoNow, its previous standalone streaming service, into the platform in 2021, keeping the name Vudu for the <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/vudu-fandangonow-merge-111549415.html">resulting product</a> .</p><p> The companies didn&#39;t reveal any business details of the handoff. “As we continue to evolve our business and remain focused on Making Movies Better by enhancing the theatrical experience, we&#39;re even more excited to expand our relationship with a trusted partner, who will ensure a continued preeminent experience for those consumers who are streaming their post-theatrical movies at home,” said Nikkole Denson-Randolph, AMC Senior VP of Content Strategy &amp; Inclusive Programming.</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/amc-transfers-its-on-demand-streaming-users-to-vudu-140033151.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/amc-transfers-its-on-demand-streaming-users-to-vudu-140033151.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 54a02329-0c1b-49b5-a097-0be10e7f2d9e</guid><dc:creator>威尔尚克林</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Thu, 01 Jun 2023 14:00:33 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1685550854</ingested><modified> 2023-05-31T16:34:40+00:00</modified><category><![CDATA[Professional Services]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Will Shanklin]]></category><media:content height="2592" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-05/f9b44440-ffce-11ed-bdf1-0aee7d37f695" width="3888"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="2592" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-05/f9b44440-ffce-11ed-bdf1-0aee7d37f695" width="3888"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[SOPA Images via Getty Images]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[UKRAINE - 2021/08/31: In this photo illustration a Vudu logo of a digital video store and streaming service is seen on a smartphone. (Photo Illustration by Pavlo Gonchar/SOPA Images/LightRocket via Getty Images)]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[In this photo illustration a Vudu logo of a digital video...]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The best password managers for 2023]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> You might&#39;ve seen password managers in the news recently because of the <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://blog.lastpass.com/2022/12/notice-of-recent-security-incident/">breach affecting LastPass customers</a> . We need to trust that all of our logins, banking credentials and other sensitive information has been neatly locked away, only accessible by us when we need it. But most tech is fallible, and the benefits of unique, strong passwords across your online presence outweigh the risks. Password managers remain a great way to securely store all of the credentials you need on a regular basis. We tested out nine of the best password managers available now to help you choose the right one for your needs.</p><h2> How do password managers work?</h2><p> Think of password managers like virtual safe deposit boxes. They hold your valuables, in this case usually online credentials, in a section of the vault only accessible to you by security key or a master password. Most of these services have autofill features that make it convenient to log in to any site without needing to remember every password you have, and they keep your credit card information close for impulse purchases.</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> But given that passwords are one of the <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.cisa.gov/news-events/news/choosing-and-protecting-passwords">top ways to keep your online identity secure</a> , the real value of password managers is staying safe online. “It&#39;s just not possible without a password manager to have unique, long and hard-to-guess passwords,” Florian Schaub, an associate professor of information and of electrical engineering and computer science at the University of Michigan, said.</p><p> Common guidance states that passwords should be unique, with the longest number of characters allowed and uppercase letters, lowercase letters, numbers and special characters. This is the exact opposite of using the same password everywhere, with minor variations depending on a site&#39;s requirements. Think of how many sites you have credentials on — it&#39;s an impossible task to remember it all without somewhere to store them safely (no, a sticky note on your desk won&#39;t cut it). Password managers are more readily accessible and offer the benefit of filling in those long passwords for you.</p><h2> Are password managers safe?</h2><p> It seems counterintuitive to store all your sensitive information in one place. One hack could mean you lose it all to an attacker and struggle for months or even years to rebuild your online presence, not to mention you may have to cancel credit cards and other accounts. But most experts in the field agree that password managers are a generally secure and safe way to keep track of your data, and the benefits of strong, complex passwords outweigh the possible risks.</p><p> The mechanics of keeping those passwords safe differs slightly from provider to provider. Generally, you have a lengthy, complex “master password” that safeguards the rest of your information. In some cases, you might also get a “security key” to enter when you log in to new devices. This is a random string of letters, numbers and symbols that the company will send you at sign up. Only you know this key, and because it&#39;s stored locally on your device or printed out on paper, it&#39;s harder for hackers to find.</p><p> These multiple layers of security make it difficult for an attacker to get into your vault even if your password manager provider experiences a breach. But the company should also follow a few security basics. A “zero-knowledge” policy means that the company keeps none of your data on file, so in the event of an attack, there&#39;s nothing for hackers to find. Regular pentests and security audits keep the company up to par on best practices, and other efforts like bug bounty programs or hosting on an open source website encourage constant vigilance for security flaws. Most password managers now also offer some level of encryption falling under the Advanced Encryption Standard (AES). AES 256-bit is the strongest, because there are the most number of possible combinations, but AES 128-bit or 192-bit are still good.</p><h2> Who are password managers for?</h2><p> Given their universal benefit, pretty much everyone could use a password manager. They&#39;re not just for the tech-savvy people or businesses anymore because so much sensitive information ends up online behind passwords, from our bank accounts to our Netflix watch history.</p><p> That&#39;s the other perk of password managers: safe password sharing. Families, friends or roommates can use them to safely access joint accounts. Texting a password to someone isn&#39;t secure, and you can help your family break the habit by starting to use one yourself, Lisa Plaggemier, executive director at National Cyber Security Alliance, said. Streaming is the obvious use case, but consider the shared bills, file storage and other sites you share access with the people around you as well.</p><h2> Are password managers worth it?</h2><p> You likely already use a password manager, even if you wouldn&#39;t think to call it that. Most phones and web browsers include a log of saved credentials on the device, like the “passwords” keychain in the settings of an iPhone. That means you&#39;ve probably seen the benefits of not having to memorize passwords or even type them out already.</p><p> While that&#39;s a great way in, the downfall of these built-in options are that they tend to be device specific. If you rely on an Apple password manager, for example, that works if you&#39;re totally in the Apple ecosystem — but you become limited once you get an Android tablet, Lujo Bauer, professor of electrical and computer engineering, and of computer science, at Carnegie Mellon University, said. If you use different devices for work and personal use and want a secure way to share passwords with others, or just don&#39;t want to be tied to one brand forever, a third-party password manager is usually worth it.</p><h2>我们如何测试</h2><p>We tested password managers by downloading each of the nine contenders on iPhone, Android, Safari, Chrome and Firefox. That helped us better understand what platforms each manager was available on, and see how support differs across operating systems and browsers.</p><p> As we got set up with each, we took note of how they iterated on the basic features of autofill and password generators. Nearly all password managers have these features, but some place limits on how much you can store while others give more control over creating easy-to-type yet complex passwords. From there, we looked at extra features like data-breach monitoring to understand which managers offered the most for your money.</p><p> Finally, we reviewed publicly available information about security specs for each. This includes LastPass, which more experts are shying away from recommending after the recent breach. For the sake of this review, we&#39;ve decided not to recommend LastPass at this time as fallout from the breach still comes to light (The company <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.wired.com/story/lastpass-engineer-breach-security-roundup/">disclosed a second incident earlier this year</a> where an unauthorized attack accessed the company&#39;s cloud storage, including sensitive data).</p><h2> Password managers we tested</h2><ul><li><p> <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:1Password;elmt:;cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=29d07367-7ffa-4e05-9a7f-c1dd19430630&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=1Password&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiIyOWQwNzM2Ny03ZmZhLTRlMDUtOWE3Zi1jMWRkMTk0MzA2MzAiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly8xcGFzc3dvcmQuY29tLyIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiYTY0OWQ5ZDYtMTBjMy0zNWFmLTk0YzItZGZlOTE5MjUxNTZhIn0&amp;signature=AQAAAedaFskljJO_nkmkybdzZwHxi54DX1OYVqiYqmgVWc-l&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2F1password.com%2F" class="rapid-with-clickid">1Password</a></p></li><li><p> <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:LastPass;elmt:;cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=4a567016-57fd-42ff-9497-6b31b5e02642&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=LastPass&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI0YTU2NzAxNi01N2ZkLTQyZmYtOTQ5Ny02YjMxYjVlMDI2NDIiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubGFzdHBhc3MuY29tLyIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiYTY0OWQ5ZDYtMTBjMy0zNWFmLTk0YzItZGZlOTE5MjUxNTZhIn0&amp;signature=AQAAARUxclm_QfTK0YNXnEiTcVaTUqctLb2EB9MVtaTUI3yG&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.lastpass.com%2F" class="rapid-with-clickid">LastPass</a></p></li><li><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://bitwarden.com/">Bitwarden</a></p></li><li><p> <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Dashlane;elmt:;cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=05a8faef-22e0-48ab-a365-0cc59778dc54&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Dashlane&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiIwNWE4ZmFlZi0yMmUwLTQ4YWItYTM2NS0wY2M1OTc3OGRjNTQiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZGFzaGxhbmUuY29tLyIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiYTY0OWQ5ZDYtMTBjMy0zNWFmLTk0YzItZGZlOTE5MjUxNTZhIn0&amp;signature=AQAAATgyIRk0s8jpy1K1ohYYrEeJBH8EG2HW8Y3B-l7cs7a-&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dashlane.com%2F" class="rapid-with-clickid">Dashlane</a></p></li><li><p> <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Keeper;elmt:;cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=f97fc99a-d04e-4e9c-b1e3-0bda0d13544b&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Keeper&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiJmOTdmYzk5YS1kMDRlLTRlOWMtYjFlMy0wYmRhMGQxMzU0NGIiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cua2VlcGVyc2VjdXJpdHkuY29tLyIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiYTY0OWQ5ZDYtMTBjMy0zNWFmLTk0YzItZGZlOTE5MjUxNTZhIn0&amp;signature=AQAAATagnPUDavwM7vNp3EMHBzMGgPTwHStvKr2uslYBnc_i&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.keepersecurity.com%2F" class="rapid-with-clickid">Keeper</a></p></li><li><p> <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL25vcmRwYXNzLmNvbS8iLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6ImE2NDlkOWQ2LTEwYzMtMzVhZi05NGMyLWRmZTkxOTI1MTU2YSJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAXc3dvFt_FBTUl4eh8nwWwcOj_8uRtp4H_WvfMoCusWk&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fnordpass.com%2F" class="rapid-with-clickid">NordPass</a></p></li><li><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://www.enpass.io/">Enpass</a></p></li><li><p> <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;cpos:11;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL215Lm5vcnRvbi5jb20vZXh0c3BhL3Bhc3N3b3JkbWFuYWdlciIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiYTY0OWQ5ZDYtMTBjMy0zNWFmLTk0YzItZGZlOTE5MjUxNTZhIn0&amp;signature=AQAAAWsN1q8IXBPU6hicsqTfsyaKAXp5TK7I6YbWqIudcDr6&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fmy.norton.com%2Fextspa%2Fpasswordmanager" class="rapid-with-clickid">Norton password manager</a></p></li><li><p> <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;cpos:12;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL2xvZ21lb25jZS5jb20vIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiJhNjQ5ZDlkNi0xMGMzLTM1YWYtOTRjMi1kZmU5MTkyNTE1NmEifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAR7AFD-nCuscZsY2B0g8D6XKA2e4UzrodET28_ZSzBBN&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Flogmeonce.com%2F" class="rapid-with-clickid">LogMeOnce</a></p></li></ul><h2> Best password manager: 1Password </h2><p><core-commerce id="d02489763f8646d988255aa794bca9a9" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> Many security experts trust <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:1Password;elmt:;cpos:13;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=29d07367-7ffa-4e05-9a7f-c1dd19430630&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=1Password&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiIyOWQwNzM2Ny03ZmZhLTRlMDUtOWE3Zi1jMWRkMTk0MzA2MzAiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly8xcGFzc3dvcmQuY29tLyIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiYTY0OWQ5ZDYtMTBjMy0zNWFmLTk0YzItZGZlOTE5MjUxNTZhIn0&amp;signature=AQAAAedaFskljJO_nkmkybdzZwHxi54DX1OYVqiYqmgVWc-l&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2F1password.com%2F" class="rapid-with-clickid">1Password</a> with their private information and, after testing it out, it&#39;s clear why. The service includes industry standard encryption, a “secret key” that only you know on top of your master password, a zero-knowledge policy that means it keeps no data, and other security features like frequent audits and a bug bounty program.</p><p> Plus, it has a pretty intuitive feel. A tutorial at download helps you import passwords from other managers onto 1Password so that you don&#39;t feel like you&#39;re starting over from scratch. It also clearly rates the strength of each password and has an “open and fill” option in the vault so that you can get into your desired site even more quickly. We also liked the option to scan a set up code to easily connect your account to your mobile devices without too much tedious typing.</p><p> At $3 per month, the individual subscription comes with unlimited passwords, items and one gigabyte of document storage for your vault. It also lets you share passwords, credit card information and other saved credentials. If you upgrade to the family plan for $5 each month, you&#39;ll get to invite up to five people (plus more for $1 each per month) to be a part of the vault.</p><ul><li><p> <strong>Number of tiers:</strong> 4</p></li><li><p> <strong>Pricing:</strong> $3/month for Individual, $5/month for Families, $20/month for Teams Starter Pack, $8/month per user for Business</p></li></ul><h2> Best free password manager: Bitwarden </h2><p><core-commerce id="ff15057c13134c979a0870b47876b8d3" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:14;pos:1" href="https://bitwarden.com/">Bitwarden&#39;s</a> free plan includes unlimited passwords on an unlimited number of devices, which is more than we&#39;ve seen from some of its competitors. There are drawbacks like you can only share vault items with one other user, but we think that&#39;s a fair tradeoff.</p><p> Bitwarden is based on open-source code, meaning anyone on GitHub can audit it, which is a good measure of security. On a personal level, it includes security audits of your information, like a data breach report, that can keep you in the know about when your passwords have been leaked and when it&#39;s time to change them. Plus, it&#39;s widely available across the platforms we tested with a level of customization, options to access your vault and more.</p><p> Bitwarden may be the best free password manager, but it does have a paid version and we do think it&#39;s worth it. At $10 annually for individuals or $40 for families, you unlock encrypted file storage, emergency access, unlimited sharing and more. But the free version comes with the basics that can get anyone set up on password management easily.</p><ul><li><p> <strong>Number of tiers:</strong> 3</p></li><li><p> <strong>Pricing:</strong> Free, $3/month per user for Teams Organization, $5/month per user for Enterprise Organization</p></li></ul><h2> Best cross-platform availability: NordPass </h2><p><core-commerce id="a86204c6b5004ba0a5c0cd3571100c6e" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> Across password managers we tested, cross-platform availability was relatively similar. Most are widely available across web browsers and different operating systems, including our other top picks on this list. But we wanted to give a nod to <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;cpos:15;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL25vcmRwYXNzLmNvbS8iLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6ImE2NDlkOWQ2LTEwYzMtMzVhZi05NGMyLWRmZTkxOTI1MTU2YSJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAXc3dvFt_FBTUl4eh8nwWwcOj_8uRtp4H_WvfMoCusWk&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fnordpass.com%2F" class="rapid-with-clickid">NordPass</a> here because of how easy the service makes it to access your vault from any platform.</p><p> NordPass has a free option with unlimited passwords and syncs across devices. A $2-per-month premium subscription keeps you logged in when switching devices, comes with security notifications and allows for item sharing. A family subscription comes with six premium accounts and only costs $4 per month. This makes it a pretty good budget option as well. Besides the pairing code to connect accounts, NordPass is a pretty standard password manager. Scanning a code gets me from my laptop to mobile device to work computer super easily. If you&#39;re constantly switching devices and those extra few seconds save your sanity, it&#39;s worth considering.</p><ul><li><p> <strong>Number of tiers:</strong> 3</p></li><li><p> <strong>Pricing:</strong> Free, $2/per month for Premium, $4/month for Family</p></li></ul><h2> Best for shared access: Dashlane </h2><p><core-commerce id="e512d97e6be44fba96f1362969567b59" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Dashlane;elmt:;cpos:16;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=05a8faef-22e0-48ab-a365-0cc59778dc54&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Dashlane&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiIwNWE4ZmFlZi0yMmUwLTQ4YWItYTM2NS0wY2M1OTc3OGRjNTQiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZGFzaGxhbmUuY29tLyIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiYTY0OWQ5ZDYtMTBjMy0zNWFmLTk0YzItZGZlOTE5MjUxNTZhIn0&amp;signature=AQAAATgyIRk0s8jpy1K1ohYYrEeJBH8EG2HW8Y3B-l7cs7a-&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dashlane.com%2F" class="rapid-with-clickid">Dashlane</a> has four subscription options: A free user gets access to one device with unlimited passwords; an advanced user pays $3 per month to get upgraded to unlimited devices and dark web monitoring; for $5 per month, a premium user also gets VPN access and an $7.49-per-month family plan includes access for up to 10 people.</p><p> It met all the criteria we looked for, but with a clear emphasis on sharing credentials. Dashlane highlights “secure sharing” starting at its free level, which is a feature that some competitors keep behind a paywall. Access for up to 10 members in a family plan is one of the bigger plans we&#39;ve seen as well. While we were testing it, password sharing seemed front of mind with a tab dedicated to it in Dashlane&#39;s browser extension. Arguably the biggest caveat here, though, is lack of Linux support.</p><ul><li><p> <strong>Number of tiers:</strong> 4</p></li><li><p> <strong>Pricing:</strong> Free, $3/month for Advanced, $5/month for Premium, $7/month for Friends and Family</p></li></ul> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/best-password-manager-134639599.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/best-password-manager-134639599.html